(48, 54, 'Millennium Development Goals Tables', 'MDG Tables', 'Millennium Development Goals tables provide data for MDG indicators from 1990 to the most recent year available in five year increments.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/embed int/MDG Table/id/c658ae98 inf n', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National, Regional', 217, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Aid Effectiveness, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development, Trade, Urban Development', 'Quarterly', 'April, July, September, December', '17 Apr 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Query tool', '', 'World Development Indicators, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/MDGs tables', 13, '1990   2015', '0', '', ''),
(49, 55, 'Country Profiles', 'CP', 'Country profiles present the latest key development data drawn from the World Development Indicators (WDI) database, the World Bank s primary database for cross country comparable development data.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/embed int/CountryProfile/id/b450fd57', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 214, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Aid Effectiveness, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development, Trade, Urban Development', 'Quarterly', 'April, July, September, December', '17 Apr 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Query tool', '', 'World Development Indicators, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/country profiles', 527, '2000   2016', '0', '', ''),
(50, 56, 'World Bank Projects & Operations', '', '<p>World Bank Projects & Operations provides access to basic information on all of the World Bank s lending projects from 1947 to the present. The dataset includes basic information such as the project title, task manager, country, project id, sector, themes, commitment amount, product line, procurement notices, contract awards, and financing. It also provides links to publicly disclosed online documents.</p>\n<p>For older projects, there is a link to the Archives catalog, which contains records ', 'http://www.worldbank.org/projects', 'Transactions', 'English', 'Day', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'Project', 0, 'Aid Effectiveness, World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Daily', 'Daily', 'Current', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Data are organized around the concept of project with the project id being the key linking the project to related operational datasets such as contract awards, loans/credits/grants, trust funds, etc.', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'Projects & Operations (XML) http://search.worldbank.org/api/projects/all.xml xml;Projects & Operations (CSV) http://search.worldbank.org/api/projects/all.csv csv', 'Projects & Operations, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/projects portfolio', 60, '1947   Current', '1', 'http://search.worldbank.org/api/v2/projects', ''),
(51, 58, 'International Debt Statistics: Summary and Country Tables', '', 'Special summary tables present cross country comparisons of key debt statistics and composition of total external debt stocks.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/gdf tables', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 129, 'External Debt', 'No further updates planned', '', '27 Sep 2010', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Query tool', '', 'Global Development Finance, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/gdf tables', 0, '', '0', '', ''),
(52, 59, 'AidFlows', '', '<p>A new tool that allows users to visualize sources and uses of development funding, by country. AidFlows offers new transparency about the flow of development funds     from countries providing the resources to countries receiving these funds.</p>\n<p> Beyond global aid data, there is information about development funds flowing through multilaterals.  The World Bank and Asian Development Bank have windows on AidFlows for institution specific data on flows. The Inter American Development Bank ha', 'http://www.aidflows.org', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Other, Regional', 210, 'Aid Effectiveness', 'No fixed schedule', 'No fixed schedule', '20 Aug 2013', 'data@worldbank.org', 'OECD data are at times    preliminary    until updated for final annual numbers.', 'Query tool', '', 'AidFlows, The World Bank, Asian Development Bank, OECD', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/aidflows', 25, '2002   2012', '0', '', ''),
(53, 61, 'World Integrated Trade Solution', 'WITS', 'WITS is a trade software tool giving access to bilateral trade between countries based on various product classifications, product details, years, and trade flows. It also contains tariff and non tariff measures data, as well as analysis tool to calculate effects of tariff reductions. In addition, users have access to many visualization tools.', 'http://wits.worldbank.org/redirect2countryprofile.aspx', 'Time series', 'English', 'Quarter', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 219, 'Trade', 'Quarterly', '', '27 Apr 2017', 'wits@worldbank.org', 'Trade imports, exports, re imports, re exports, gross exports, gross imports, MFN tariff rates, bound tariff raters, preferential tariffs. Non Tariff Measure data with new UNCTAD classification now available.', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'WITS http://wits.worldbank.org/data/public/cp/WITS_Trade_Summary_AllCountries_AllYears.zip', 'United Nations COMTRADE database, UNCTAD s TRAINS database, WTO s Integrated database (IDB), WTO s consolidated tariff schedules (CTS), World Bank and the Center for International Business, Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth College   s Global Preferential Trade Access Database (GPTAD)', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wits', 80, '1962   2015', '0', 'http://wits.worldbank.org/witsapiintro.aspx', ''),
(54, 62, 'Migration and Remittances Factbook 2011', '', 'Migration and Remittances Factbook 2011 provides a snapshot of migration and remittances for all countries, regions and income groups of the world, compiled from available data from various sources.', 'http://go.worldbank.org/092X1CHHD0', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 210, 'Labor & Social Protection', 'Annually', 'Every 2 3 years', '31 Oct 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Country tables contain data for migration and remittance related indicators for selected years. Excel files include data for inward and outward remittance flows from 1970 to 2010 and data are updated twice a year. The factbook is published every 2 to 3 years.', 'Query tool, Bulk download', 'Remittances inflows (Excel) http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTPROSPECTS/Resources/334934 1110315015165/RemittancesData_Inflows_Apr12(Public).xlsx excel;Remittances outflows (Excel) http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTPROSPECTS/Resources/334934 1110315015165/RemittancesData_Outflows_Apr12(Publi', 'Migration and Remittances Factbook 2011, The World Bank.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/migration and remittances', 85, '2000   2010', '0', '', ''),
(55, 63, 'Quarterly Public Sector Debt', 'QPSD', '<p>Quarterly Public Sector Debt (QPSD) database, jointly developed by the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund, brings together detailed public sector debt data of selected countries. </p>\n<p>The QPSD database includes country and cross country tables, and specific public debt components. The data represent the following sectors on an as available basis: General government; otherwise Central government; otherwise Budgetary central government; Nonfinancial public corporations and Financ', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source public sector', 'Time series', 'English', 'Quarter', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 101, 'External Debt, Public Sector', 'Quarterly', 'January, April, July, October', '01 Nov 2017', 'erucaj@worldbank.org, rkoehler@imf.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', 'Public Sector Debt Statistics, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/quarterly public sector debt', 8, '1995   2017', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '20'),
(56, 64, 'The Changing Wealth of Nations', '', 'The Wealth of Nations dataset provides country level data on comprehensive wealth, as published in  The Changing Wealth of Nations  (2011). It presents a set of    comprehensive wealth accounts    for over 150 countries for 1995, 2000, and 2005, which allows a longer term assessment of global, regional, and country performance in building wealth.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 150, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Environment, Financial Sector', 'No further updates planned', '', '20 Jan 2011', '', 'Wealth estimates are calculated for 3 years: 1995, 2000, and 2005. Adjusted net saving and non renewable resource rent indicators are calculated annually from 1970 to 2008. Please note that updated annual data for adjusted net saving and resource rents are available at http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wealth accounting.', 'Bulk download', 'Wealth of Nations (XLS 655KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/total_and_per_capita_wealth_of_nations.xls excel', 'The Changing Wealth of Nations, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wealth of nations', 51, '1995   2005', '0', '', ''),
(57, 65, 'East Asia and Pacific Economic Update', 'EAP', 'The East Asia and Pacific Economic Update is the comprehensive, twice yearly review of the region   s economies prepared by the East Asia and Pacific region of the World Bank. The report provides forward looking analysis of the region s economic and social well being, and includes data on key indicators for output, employment, prices, public sector, foreign trade, BOP, external debt and financial markets.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, LMY, IDA, IBRD', 'National', 12, 'Economy & Growth, Trade', 'Biannually', 'Spring and fall', '30 Apr 2014', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Data for 2011 are estimated, and data for 2012 and 2013 are forecast.', 'Bulk download', 'Key Indicators http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/eap update may 2012 key indicators.xls xls;Appendix Tables (PDF 206.5KB) http://data.worldbank.org/sites/default/files/eap update may 2012 appendixes.pdf pdf;', 'East Asia and Pacific Economic Update, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/eap economic update', 38, '2007   2013', '0', '', ''),
(58, 66, 'Arab World Education Performance Indicators', 'AWEI', 'The Arab World Education Performance Indicators compiles data on education outcomes in 22 Arab States member countries in an aggregated and standardized manner. It allows users to compare the performance of each country along the following 6 important dimensions of education performance: access, equity, quality, efficiency, relevance, and Knowledge Economy readiness.', 'http://go.worldbank.org/IJ32PVICB0', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'MNA, IBRD, HIC, SSA, LMY, IDA', 'National', 22, 'Education', 'No further updates planned', '', '01 Apr 2010', 'awei@worldbank.org', '', 'Query tool', '', 'Arab World Education Indicators, The World Bank.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/arab world education indicators', 1, '2000   2009', '0', '', ''),
(59, 67, 'MIGA Project Portfolio', 'MIGA', 'The Multilateral Investment Guarantee Agency (MIGA) was created in 1988 as a member of the World Bank Group to promote foreign direct investment into emerging economies to support economic growth, reduce poverty, and improve people   s lives. MIGA fulfills this mandate by offering political risk insurance (guarantees) to investors and lenders, covering risks including expropriation, breach of contract, currency transfer restriction, war and civil disturbance, and non honoring of sovereign financ', 'https://www.miga.org/Pages/Projects/searchresults.aspx', 'Time series', 'English', 'Day', 'SAS, LMY, IDA, ECA, IBRD, MNA, SSA, LAC, HIC, EAP', 'Project', 179, 'World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Weekly', '', 'Current', 'migainquiry@worldbank.org', 'Data are available for all projects supported by MIGA since 1988.', 'Query tool', '', 'Multilateral Investment Guarantee Agency   World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/miga projects', 7, '1988   Current', '0', '', ''),
(60, 68, 'Mapping for Results', '', '<p>Mapping for Results aims to visualize the locations of Bank activities and to provide access to information about indicators, sectors, funding, and results.</p>\n<p>The main objectives of the program are (i) to support the monitoring and reporting of results by providing users with an analytical tool to analyze and visualize the geographic location of Bank activities at the sub national level; (ii) to improve aid effectiveness by enhanced transparency and accountability of donor funded operati', 'http://maps.worldbank.org', 'Geospatial', 'English', 'Annual', 'SAS, LMY, IDA, ECA, IBRD, MNA, SSA, LAC, EAP, HIC', 'Project, Sub national', 81, 'World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'No further updates planned', '', '08 Feb 2011', 'maps@worldbank.org', 'Data on sector distribution, list of financed activities, and number/volume of active financed activities of Bank financed activities under all 12    lending    product lines. Out of these activities, 1264 activities have been mapped by the Spring Meetings 2011 under the following product lines: IBRD/IDA, Global Environment Project, Special Financing, Montreal Protocol, GEF Medium Sized Programs, Guarantees, Debt Reduction Facility, and Carbon Offsets. More than 16,520 specific project locations', 'API, Query tool', '', 'Mapping for Results, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/mapping for results', 0, '', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', ''),
(61, 69, 'Socio Economic Database for Latin America and the Caribbean', 'SEDLAC', '<p>This web site includes statistics on poverty and other distributional and social variables from 25 Latin American and Caribbean (LAC) countries. All statistics are computed from microdata of the main household surveys carried out in these countries using a homogenous methodology (data permitting).</p>\n<p> SEDLAC allows users to monitor the trends in poverty and other distributional and social indicators in the region. The database is available in the form of brief reports, charts and electron', 'http://sedlac.econo.unlp.edu.ar/eng/dynamics searches.php', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'LAC, IBRD, HIC, IDA, LMY', 'National', 24, 'Poverty, Education, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection', 'Biannually', 'Fall and Spring', '23 Jun 2015', 'sedlac@cedlas.org', 'In each period the sample of countries represents more than 97  of LAC total population. The database mainly covers the 1990s and 2000s, although we also present information for previous decades in a few countries. Statistics are updated periodically.', 'Query tool', '', 'SEDLAC (CEDLAS and The World Bank) or  Socio Economic Database for Latin America and the Caribbean (CEDLAS and The World Bank) .', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/sedlac', 6, '1974   2013', '0', '', ''),
(62, 70, 'Landmine Contamination, Casualties and Clearance Database', 'LC3D', 'The Landmine Contamination, Casualties and Clearance provides country level data on a broad range of issues related to landmines and cluster munitions, including contamination, casualties and clearance, and their associated cost. The data was compiled from two sources: Landmine and Cluster Munition Monitor and annual surveys by the United Nations Mine Action Team (UNMAT).', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source landmine', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 202, 'Labor & Social Protection, Social Development', 'No fixed schedule', '', '16 Aug 2013', 'kanye@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'LC3 dataset (638kb) http://data.worldbank.org/sites/default/files/data/lc3d dataset.xls excel;LC3 dataset (591kb) http://data.worldbank.org/sites/default/files/data/lc3d dataset.csv csv;Terminology (PDF 246KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Terminology.pdf pdf', 'Landmine Contamination, Casualties and Clearance Database, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/landmine database', 0, '1999   2009', '0', '', ''),
(63, 71, 'World Development Report 2011', 'WDR2011', 'As a follow up to the official launch of the 2011 World Development Report on Conflict, Security and Development (WDR 2011), the WDR 2011 database has been launched. The database includes statistics related to civil war, terrorism, and trafficking, as well as socio economic, demographic and political data. It is a collection of diverse data from multi sources into a single easily navigable depository. The database is a basic research tool for academics and practitioners which brings together div', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 211, 'Labor & Social Protection, Public Sector, Social Development', 'No further updates planned', 'April', '28 Apr 2011', 'kanye@worldbank.org', 'The data in this database are taken from public sources.', 'Bulk download', 'WDR2011 Dataset (XLSX 6.24MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/WDR2011 Dataset.xlsx excel;WDR2011 Dataset (CSV 2.95MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/WDR2011 Dataset.csv csv;WDR2011 Codebook (PDF 344KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/WDR2011 CodeBook.pdf', 'World Development Report 2011, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wdr2011', 40, '1960   2009', '0', '', ''),
(64, 73, 'Global Bilateral Migration Database', 'GBMD', '<p>Global matrices of bilateral migrant stocks spanning the period 1960 2000, disaggregated by gender and based primarily on the foreign born concept are presented. Over one thousand census and population register records are combined to construct decennial matrices corresponding to the last five completed census rounds.</p>\n<p> For the first time, a comprehensive picture of bilateral global migration over the last half of the twentieth century emerges. The data reveal that the global migrant st', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source global bilateral migration', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 226, 'Labor & Social Protection', 'Annually', '2014', '01 Jul 2011', 'cozden@worldbank.org', '', 'Query tool', '', 'Global Bilateral Migration Database, World Bank Group and   .   zden, C. Parsons, M. Schiff and T. L. Walmsley (2011)  Where on Earth is Everybody  The Evolution of Global Bilateral Migration, 1960 2000 , World Bank Economic Review 25(1):12 56', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/global bilateral migration database', 16, '1960   2000', '0', '', ''),
(65, 74, 'Population ranking', 'POP', 'Population ranking table.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 217, 'Health', 'Quarterly', 'April, July, September, December', '01 Jul 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Rankings are based on available data only.', 'Bulk download', 'POP (Excel) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/POP.xls excel;POP (CSV) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/POP.csv csv;POP (PDF) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/POP.pdf pdf', 'World Development Indicators, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/Population ranking table', 105, '2016', '0', '', ''),
(66, 75, 'Bolivia Agricultural Public Expenditure Review', 'Bolivia APER', 'This is one of the most comprehensive datasets on public spending in the agricultural sector in Bolivia. The data on agriculture and agriculture related expenditures was derived from the national accounting data obtained from the Public Accounting Department of the Ministry of Economy and Public Finance of Bolivia. The data is disaggregated by function (such as research and extension, irrigation, rural roads, rural electrification, etc.), economic classification (capital and current) and level o', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'LAC, LMY, IDA', 'National, Sub national', 0, 'Agriculture & Rural Development', 'No further updates planned', '', '02 Sep 2011', '', '', 'Bulk download', 'Bolivia APER  (26 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Bolivia APER.xlsx excel', 'Public Accounting Department of the Ministry of Economy and Public Finance of Bolivia', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/bolivia aper', 0, '1996   2008', '0', '', ''),
(67, 76, 'IEG World Bank Project Performance Ratings', 'IEG WB Project Ratings', 'This dataset contains all World Bank project assessments carried out by the Independent Evaluation Group (IEG) since the unit was created back in the 70   s. Spanning over 30 years, the collection has more than 11,300 project assessments, covering more than 9,600 completed projects; it is perhaps the longest running and most comprehensive project performance data collection of its kind. IEG website: http://ieg.worldbankgroup.org/ratings.', 'https://finances.worldbank.org/dataset/IEG World Bank Project Performance Ratings/rq9d pctf', 'Time series', 'English', 'Day', 'EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'Project', 170, 'World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Quarterly', '', '17 Nov 2017', 'ieg@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'IEG (Excel) https://finances.worldbank.org/api/views/rq9d pctf/rows.csv accessType DOWNLOAD&bom true;', 'IEG World Bank Project Performance Ratings, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/IEG', 6, '1964   2014', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers/world bank finances', ''),
(68, 77, 'Health Nutrition and Population Statistics by Wealth Quintile', '', 'This database presents HNP data by wealth quintile since 1990s to present. It covers more than 70 indicators, including childhood diseases and interventions, nutrition, sexual and reproductive health, mortality, and other determinants of health, for more than 90 low  and middle income countries. The data sources are Demographic and Health Surveys (DHS) and Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys (MICS).', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source health nutrition and population statistics by wealth quintile', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Sub national', 90, 'Health', 'Annually', 'December', '18 Dec 2017', 'data@worldbank.org      healthpop@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'HNP by Wealth Quintile (CSV) ZIP (1.6 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/hnpq_csv.zip csv;HNP by Wealth Quintile (Excel) ZIP (1.3 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/hnpq_excel.zip excel;New Sectoral Commitments by FY & Region (37Kb) http://datatopics.worldbank.org/hnp/files', 'Health Nutrition and Population Statistics by Wealth Quintile, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/HNPquintile', 19, '1960   2017', '0', '', '39'),
(69, 78, 'Open Data for the Horn', '', 'Open Data for the Horn facilitates open access to geospatial information, data and knowledge sources, about the ongoing response to the drought in the Horn of Africa. Open Data for the Horn is a project of the Open Data for Resilience Initiative, a global partnership that seeks to build data sharing programs along with the capacity and tools to use data to make more informed decisions, that is working on implementation in 25 countries.', 'http://horn.rcmrd.org/data/search', 'Geospatial', 'English', 'Annual', 'SSA', 'Sub national', 9, 'Poverty', 'No further updates planned', '', '21 Nov 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Query tool', '', 'Open Data for the Horn, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/open data for the horn', 0, '2006   2011', '0', '', ''),
(70, 79, 'Haiti Data', '', '<p>HaitaData.org facilitates open access to Haiti related geo spatial information, data and knowledge sources, encouraging others to share and use them for the development of Haiti. The data can be used for many purposes: establishing baseline data, conducting risk assessments, planning, project monitoring, and tracking progress. </p>\n<p>This site is intended to facilitate more effective support to the country   s rehabilitation, recovery and longer  term sustainable development. HaitiData.org i', 'http://haitidata.org/layers', 'Geospatial', 'English', 'Annual', 'LAC, LMY, IDA', 'Sub national', 1, 'Climate Change', 'No further updates planned', '', '21 Nov 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', 'This project contains a diverse set of geospatial (GIS) data for Haiti, including topology, geology, natural features, infrastructure, and incidence of natural disasters.', 'Query tool', '', 'Haiti Data, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/haiti data', 2, '1998   2010', '0', '', ''),
(71, 80, 'Climate Change Data', '', 'Data from World Development Indicators and Climate Change Knowledge Portal on climate systems, exposure to climate impacts, resilience, greenhouse gas emissions, and energy use.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 213, 'Climate Change', 'No fixed schedule', '', '21 Nov 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download', 'Climate Change (Excel) (4.6 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/climate_change_download_0.xls xls;', 'Climate Change Data, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/climate change', 130, '1990   2011', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', ''),
(72, 81, 'Wage Bill and Pay Compression', '', '<p>Wage Bill and Pay Compression provides data on public sector wage bills, pay compression, and government employment. Wage bill includes both central and general government compensation as percentages of GDP, revenues, and expenditures.</p>\n<p> Pay compression is defined as the ratio of highest salary to lowest salary on the central government s main salary scale. Public Sector employment includes both General Government and State Owned Enterprise s employees, but only general government emplo', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 0, 'Labor & Social Protection', 'Annually', 'No fixed schedule', '23 Nov 2011', 'vsrivastava@worldbank.org', 'Wage Bill data are from 2000 to 2008. More than 150 countries are covered where data are available. Pay compression data are compiled from various sources and 34 observations are available from mid 1990s to 2008.', 'Bulk download', 'Pay Compres n http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/wage_compression_data.xls excel;Wage Bill http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/wage_bill_data_final_july_22_2011.xls excel;', 'Wage Bill and Pay Compression, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wage bill pay compression', 9, '', '0', '', ''),
(73, 82, 'Climate Change Knowledge Portal: Historical Data', 'CCKP', 'This database contains historical temperature and precipitation data aggregated from 2 degree gridded data to the country and basin levels.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Month', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 0, 'Climate Change', 'No further updates planned', '', '01 Dec 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download', 'Historical Data (Excel) (380 KB)  http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/cckp_historical_data_0.xls xls;', 'Derived from the Climate Research Unit (Mitchell et al, 2003).', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/cckp_historical_data', 25, '1961   1999', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers/climate data api', ''),
(74, 83, 'Little Data Book on Climate Change:  Supplemental Data', 'CC LDB', '<p>The World Bank s Little Data Book on Climate Change contains a diverse set of indicators covering climate, exposure to impacts, resilience, GHG emissions, national level actions and carbon markets. </p>\n<p>This supplemental dataset contains two spreadsheets: one with historical averages for the time period 1961 1990, based on gridded climatologies; and the other with projected annual averages for the years 2045 2065, relative to annual averages in the control period of 1961 2000, of ensemble ', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 245, 'Climate Change, Environment', 'No further updates planned', '', '01 Dec 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download', 'Supp. Data   EXCEL (160.00 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/ccldb_supplemental.xls xls;', 'Historical climate: Climate Research Unit (Mitchell et al, 2003). Projected changes: Climate Systems Analysis Group, University of Cape Town 2009, calculated from Meehl et al, 2007.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/ldbcc supplemental', 0, '', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', ''),
(75, 84, 'Climate For Development', '', 'Climate For Development is a map based micro site that illustrates the links between climate change and development. The site is built on the open climate data available through the Climate Change Knowledge Portal. The data used on Climate For Development may be downloaded directly from the site or as map layers via the MapBox API.', 'http://climate4development.worldbank.org/open', 'Geospatial', 'English', '', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'Other', 0, 'Climate Change', 'No further updates planned', '', '02 Dec 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', 'This project contains a diverse set of geospatial (GIS) global map layers for topics including climate, risk and vulnerability, and World Bank agricultural projects.', 'Query tool', '', 'Data in this project come from various sources.  Please refer to specific indicators for source and citation.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/climate for development', 0, '', '0', '', ''),
(76, 85, 'Climate Change Knowledge Portal:  Ensemble Projections', '', '   Ensemble    temperature and precipitation data are derived from multiple global circulation models (GCMs). The ensemble data depict the range (10th percentile, median and 90th percentile) of model outputs run under each of two scenarios, A2 and B1, for four future time periods. The first listed download contains data aggregated to the country level; the remaining downloads are gridded data in shapefile format.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Month', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 0, 'Climate Change', 'No further updates planned', '', '01 Dec 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download', 'Country Projections http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/catalog/cckp_ensemble_projections.zip zip;Temp. Averages (SHP: 32MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/ClimateChange/climate avg tas.zip zip;', 'Climate Change Knowledge Portal:  http://climateknowledgeportal.worldbank.org', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/cckp ensemble projections', 22, '', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers/climate data api', ''),
(77, 86, 'Global Economic Prospects', 'GEP', 'Country level data on the short , medium, and long term outlook for the global economy and the implications for developing countries and poverty reduction. Includes historical trends and growth forecasts.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source global economic prospects', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National, Regional', 132, 'Economy & Growth', 'Biannually', 'January, June', '16 Jan 2018', 'dpgroup@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'GEP (Excel)   ZIP (23 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/GEP_Excel.zip zip;GEP (CSV)   ZIP (13 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/GEP_CSV.zip zip', 'Global Economic Prospects, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/global economic prospects', 42, '2015 2020', '0', '', '27'),
(78, 87, 'The Atlas of Social Protection: Indicators of Resilience and Equity', 'ASPIRE', 'The World Bank   s ASPIRE online tool is the most up to date compilation of global social protection and labor (SPL) estimates, including data from 120 countries   mostly in the developing world. ASPIRE provides open and accessible household level data on populations    social and economic status; assessments of SPL programs, including weaknesses such as low coverage and poor targeting; SPL program impacts on poverty and inequality; and ways to improve household data collection for SPL programs.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/source/global social protection', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA', 'National, Regional', 147, 'Labor & Social Protection, Poverty', 'Biannually', '', '09 May 2017', 'socialprotection@worldbank.org', 'ASPIRE contains information on almost 5 million individuals in 1.3 million households. Currently, the database includes nearly 69 harmonized household surveys for 2005 2010.', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'ASPIRE (Excel) ZIP (9 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/ASPIRE_excel.zip excel;ASPIRE (CSV) ZIP (8MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/ASPIRE_csv.zip csv', 'The Atlas of Social Protection: Indicators of Resilience and Equity, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/atlas_social_protection', 13, '1998 2015', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '29'),
(79, 88, 'Global Financial Inclusion (Global Findex) Database', 'Global Findex', '<P>The Global Financial Inclusion Database provides 800 country level indicators of financial inclusion summarized for all adults and disaggregated by key demographic characteristics gender, age, education, income, and rural residence. Covering more than 140 economies, the indicators of financial inclusion measure how people save, borrow, make payments and manage risk.</P>\n<P>The reference citation for the data is: Demirguc Kunt, Asli, Leora Klapper, Dorothe Singer, and Peter Van Oudheusden. 201', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source global findex (global financial inclusion database)', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 140, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Economy & Growth, Education, Gender, Urban Development', 'Annually', 'Every three years', '15 Apr 2015', 'data@worldbank.org', 'The Global Findex indicators are drawn from survey data collected over the 2011 and 2014 calendar year.', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'Global Findex (Excel) ZIP (6.2 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/FINDEX_excel.zip excel;Global Findex (CSV) ZIP (2.3 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/FINDEX_csv.zip csv', 'Global Financial Inclusion (Global Findex) Database, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/financial_inclusion', 42, '2011   2014', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '28'),
(80, 89, 'Corporate Scorecard 2013 Indicators', 'CSC2013', '<p>The Corporate Scorecard 2013 was designed to provide a snapshot of the Bank s overall performance, including its business modernization, in the context of development results. This archived version has been superseded by a re designed Corporate Scorecard for 2014 (pdf only).</p>\n<p>The World Bank has systems   on which it continuously improves   for measuring and monitoring both development results and its own performance. These systems are complemented by independent evaluations. With the Re', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 185, 'Public Sector, Trade', 'No further updates planned', '', '20 Dec 2013', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Data availability (number of economies, start and end date, and granularity) varies by tier. Tier 1 indicators are available via API.', 'Bulk download', 'Corporate Scorecard Indicators http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Corporate Scorecard Tier1 2 3 4.zip zip;World Bank Corporate Scorecard 2013 (PDF) (994 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/World 20Bank 20Corporate 20Scorecard.pdf PDF', 'Corporate Scorecard 2013, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/corporate scorecard 2013 indicators', 12, '1990   2012', '0', '', ''),
(81, 90, 'Exporter Dynamics Database', 'EDD', 'The Exporter Dynamics Database is the first database providing measures of exporter characteristics and dynamics across 70 countries in all geographic regions and at all income levels. The Exporter Dynamics Database contains more than 100 measures covering the basic characteristics of exporters, their distribution by size, the diversification in their products and markets, their dynamics in terms of entry, exit, and survival, and the average unit prices of the goods they trade.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/databases/edd', 'Time series;Transactions', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 70, 'Private Sector, Trade', 'No fixed schedule', 'Summer or Fall', '31 Mar 2016', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Data for the 2000s is available for all countries while longer time series covering the 1990s are available for a selected group of countries.', 'Query tool', '', 'Users of the Database please cite its source as: Fernandes, A., Freund, C. and M. Pierola (2016).    Exporter Behavior, Country Size and Stage of Development: Evidence from the Exporter Dynamics Database    Journal of Development Economics vol. 119, pp. 121 137.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/exporter dynamics database', 29, '1997   2014', '0', '', '30'),
(82, 91, 'Monitoring Gender Mainstreaming in World Bank Lending Operations', 'MGM', 'This data set determines the extent to which projects are gender informed on three dimensions: analysis, actions and monitoring and evaluation. It is updated on an annual basis.', 'https://finances.worldbank.org/dataset/Monitoring Gender Mainstreaming In World Bank Lend/cfwt ypej', 'Transactions', 'English', 'Annual', 'SAS, LMY, IDA, ECA, IBRD, EAP, HIC, SSA, LAC', 'Project', 124, 'Gender', 'No further updates planned', 'August', '25 Jun 2012', '', 'Data are available for 2010 and 2011.', 'API, Query tool', '', 'World Bank Gender and Development Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/monitoring gender mainstreaming world bank lending operations', 12, '', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', ''),
(83, 92, 'International Debt Statistics', 'IDS', 'Focuses on financial flows, trends in external debt, and other major financial indicators for low  and middle income countries. Includes over 200 time series indicators from 1970 to 2016, for most reporting countries, and pipeline data for scheduled debt service payments on existing commitments to 2024.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/Data/Views/VariableSelection/SelectVariables.aspx source International Debt Statistics', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National, Regional', 123, 'External Debt', 'Annually', 'October', '24 Oct 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'IDS (Excel) ZIP (8.5 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS_Excel.zip  excel;IDS (CSV) ZIP (3 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS_CSV.zip  csv', 'International Debt Statistics, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/international debt statistics', 302, '1970 2024', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '6'),
(84, 93, 'GPE Results Forms Database', 'GPE', 'The data originate from the education goals of developing country partners of the Global Partnership for Education (GPE). Indicators compare actual values observed against targets, as set in education sector plans, joint sector reviews, and GPE grant applications. Indicators present key education outcomes and service delivery data; domestic, external, and GPE financing; learning outcomes; the composition of the Local Education Groups; and aid effectiveness in the education sector.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source global partnership for education', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'SAS, LMY, IDA, ECA, SSA, EAP, MNA, LAC', 'National', 46, 'Aid Effectiveness, Education', 'Annually', 'No further updates planned', '10 Jan 2013', 'jbernard@globalpartnership.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', 'GPE Results Forms, Global Partnership for Education', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/global partnership for education', 4, '1995   2030', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '34'),
(85, 94, 'Trade Costs Dataset', '', 'The Trade Costs Dataset provides estimates of bilateral trade costs in agriculture and manufactured goods for the 1995 2015 period. It is built on trade and production data collected in 178 countries. Symmetric bilateral trade costs are computed using the Inverse Gravity Framework (Novy 2009), which estimates trade costs for each country pair using bilateral trade and gross national output. Trade costs are available for two sectors:  trade in manufactured goods, and agriculture. Energy is exclud', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/source/escap world bank international trade costs', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA', 'National', 178, 'Trade', 'Annually', 'Mid calendar year', '12 Jun 2017', 'jarvis1@worldbank.org', 'This is a joint project between the World Bank International Trade Department and the Trade Division at the UNESCAP.', 'Query tool', '', 'The World Bank UNESCAP Trade costs Database.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/trade costs dataset', 20, '1995   2015', '0', '', ''),
(86, 95, 'Africa s Infrastructure: Airports', 'AICD', '<p>The Africa Infrastructure Country Diagnostic (AICD) has data collection and analysis on the status of the main network infrastructures. The AICD database provides cross country data on network infrastructure for nine major sectors: air transport, information and communication technologies, irrigation, ports, power, railways, roads, water and sanitation.</p>\n<p>The indicators are defined as to cover key areas for policy making: affordability, access, pricing as well as institutional, fiscal an', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source africa infrastructure: airport', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'MNA, IBRD, SSA, IDA, LMY, HIC', 'National, Sub national, Regional', 24, 'Infrastructure', 'No further updates planned', '3 year cycle', '30 Nov 2009', 'http://www.infrastructureafrica.org/aicd/contact', '', 'Query tool', '', 'Africa s Infrastructure, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/africa infrastructure airportS', 0, '1990   2009', '0', '', ''),
