(92, 101, 'Sustainable Energy for All', 'SE4ALL', 'The    Sustainable Energy for all (SE4ALL)    initiative, launched in 2010 by the UN Secretary General,  established three global objectives to be accomplished by 2030: to ensure universal access to modern energy services, to double the global rate of improvement in global energy efficiency, and to double the share of renewable energy in the global energy mix. SE4ALL database supports this initiative and provides country level historical data for access to electricity and non solid fuel; share o', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source sustainable energy for all', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD, EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, HIC, LMY, IBRD, IDA, ', 'National', 181, 'Energy & Mining', 'No fixed schedule', '', '09 Sep 2015', 'data@worldbank.org', 'For access to electricity and to non solid fuel there are 3 data points for 1990 2000 2010', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool, ', 'SE4ALL (Excel) ZIP  http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/SE4ALL_excel.zip excel;SE4ALL (CSV) ZIP  http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/SE4ALL_csv.zip csv', 'SE4ALL database,  IEA and World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/sustainable energy for all', 49, '1990   2010', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '35'),
(93, 102, 'Poverty and Equity Database', '', '<p>Latest poverty and inequality indicators compiled from officially recognized international sources. Poverty indicators include the poverty headcount ratio, poverty gap, and number of poor at both international and national poverty lines. Inequality indicators include the Gini index and income or consumption distributions.  The database includes national, regional and global estimates.</p>\n<p>This database is maintained by the Gloabl Poverty Working Group (GPWG), a team of poverty measurement ', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source poverty and equity database', 'Time Series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SSA, SAS, LMY, IBRD, IDA, ', 'National', 169, 'Poverty', 'Quarterly', 'April, July, September, December', '24 Oct 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'PovStats (Excel)   ZIP (826 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/PovStats_excel.zip zip;PovStats (CSV)   ZIP (242 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/PovStats_csv.zip zip', 'Poverty and Equity database, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/poverty and equity database', 101, '1974   2016', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '24'),
(94, 103, 'Service Delivery Indicators', 'SDI', '<p>The Service Delivery Indicators program is an application of the principles of the 2004 World Development Report Making Services Work for Poor People. The Service Delivery Indicators project is a new Africa wide initiative that tracks service delivery in education and health across countries and over time.</p>\n<p>The project collects nationally representative data that focus mainly on performance and quality of service delivery in primary schools and at frontline health facilities. This partn', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/source/service delivery indicators', 'Time Series', '', 'Annual', 'SSA, LMY, IDA', 'Other (Facility)', 8, 'Education, Health', 'No fixed schedule', 'No fixed schedule', '11 Jan 2017', 'sdi@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'SDI (Excel)   ZIP (79 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/SDI_excel.zip zip;SDI (CSV)   ZIP (22 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/SDI_csv.zip zip', 'Service Delivery Indicators, The World Bank', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/service delivery indicators', 16, '2010   2016', '0', '', ''),
(95, 105, 'Crowd Sourced Price Collection', '', '<p>The World Bank Pilot Study for Crowd Sourced Price Data Collection through Mobile Phones combined the need for high frequency data, recent developments in information and communication technologies, and power of crowd. Crowd sourced data are data collected and reported by the user community using information and communication technologies.</p>\n<p>The objective of the pilot was to study the feasibility of crowd sourced price data collection. Non professional price collectors used personal comp', '', 'Time series', '', 'Day', 'EAP, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, SAS, SSA', 'City or metropolitan, Sub national', 8, 'Economy & Growth, Poverty', 'No further updates planned', '', '22 Aug 2013', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'Crowd Sourced Price Collection (CSV) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Crowd Sourced_Price_Collection_CSV.zip CSV;Crowd Sourced Price Collection (excel) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Crowd Sourced_Price_Collection_excel.zip excel', 'Hamadeh, N., Rissanen, M. and Yamanaka, M. (2013).  The World Bank Pilot Study for Crowd Sourced Data Collection through Mobile Phones. ', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/crowd sourced price collection', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(96, 107, 'World Development Report 2014', 'WDR 2014', 'The WDR 2014 dataset includes 75 indicators relevant to the management of risk in the context of development. These indicators are included in the data annex in the report    WDR 2014: Risk & Opportunity: Managing Risk For Development.    These indicators summarize the level and dimensions of risk facing each country, together with the capacity to manage risk along several different social, economic, financial, and environmental dimensions.', '', 'Cross sectional', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 133, 'Economy & Growth, Education, Environment, Financial Sector, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty', 'No further updates planned', '', '09 Oct 2013', 'data@worldbank.org', 'The data in this dataset are taken from a range of public sources and research datasets. Please refer to the Technical Notes in the report    WDR 2014: Risk & Opportunity: Managing Risk For Development    for more information.', 'Bulk download', 'WDR 2014 annex tables (Excel/Word)   ZIP (283 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/wdr2014 annex.zip', 'Indicators should be cited individually, as documented in the Technical Notes', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/world development report 2014', 89, '', '', '', ''),
(97, 108, 'World Report on Disability', '', 'Dataset is from the World report on disability, Technical appendix A: Estimates of disability prevalence ( ) and of years of health lost due to disability (YLD), by country.', '', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 194, 'Health, Labor & Social Protection', 'No further updates planned', '', '18 Oct 2013', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Single data point for each indicator is available. Data is frozen and will not be updated.', 'Bulk download', 'World Report on Disability (Excel) (43 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Disability_data_Annex_A.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/world report on disability', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(98, 109, 'Public Accountability Mechanisms', 'PAM', 'The Public Accountability Mechanisms (PAM) Initiative provides assessments of countries    in law and in practice efforts to enhance the transparency of public administration and the accountability of public officials.', '', 'Cross sectional;Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 90, 'Public Sector', 'No fixed schedule', 'No fixed schedule', '31 Oct 2013', 'Francesca Recanatini, Senior Public Sector Specialist, frecanatini@worldbank.org', 'Data for Taiwan, China are available.', 'Bulk download', 'Public Accountability Mechanisms (PAM) https://agidata.org/Pam/QuickLinksByAbc.aspx', 'Public Accountability Mechanisms, The World Bank. Also cite the year of the dataset.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/public accountability mechanisms', 0, '2008 2013', '', '', ''),
(99, 110, 'Subnational Malnutrition Database', '', 'Subnational estimates of child malnutrition (prevalence for stunting, underweight, overweight, wasting and severe wasting indicators) using available data up to 2012.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source subnational malnutrition database', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, IBRD, IDA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National, Sub national', 137, 'Health', 'No fixed schedule', 'N/A', '21 Mar 2016', 'Juan Feng (jfeng1@worldbank.org)', '', 'API, Query tool', '', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/subnational malnutrition database', 0, '1969 2014', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '5'),
(100, 111, 'Wealth Accounting', '', '<p>Wealth Accounting supplements macroeconomic indicators, such as Gross Domestic Product (GDP), by measuring the comprehensive wealth of a country. While changes in GDP tell us if growth is occurring, changes in wealth (i.e., saving rate) tell us if growth is sustainable that is, whether it is long term. So, just as private companies are assessed by looking at both income and balance sheets, countries need to start accounting for wealth and not just income. </p>\n<p>For the past 15 years, the Wo', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source wealth accounting', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 0, 'Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Energy & Mining, Environment', 'Annually', 'April', '16 Jun 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'Adjusted Net Savings (Excel) ZIP (2.6 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Wealth Accounting_excel.zip excel;Adjusted Net Savings (CSV) ZIP (969 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Wealth Accounting_csv.zip csv', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wealth accounting', 26, '1970 2015', '', '', '43'),
(101, 112, 'Indonesia Database for Policy and Economic Research', 'INDO DAPOER', 'The Indonesia Database for Policy and Economic Research (INDO DAPOER) contains relevant economic and social indicators at the province  and district level, which span across four main categories: fiscal, economic, social and demographic, as well as infrastructure. Please note that data and metadata are currently under review and will be revised shortly.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source 1266', 'Cross sectional;Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, IBRD, LMY', 'Sub national', 1, 'Economy & Growth, Education, Financial Sector, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Public Sector', 'No fixed schedule', 'Based on the availability of new data updates', '08 Jun 2015', 'Cut Dian   cagustina@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'INDO DAPOER (Excel)   ZIP (3.6 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/INDODAPOER_excel.zip zip;INDO DAPOER (CSV)   ZIP 2.2 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/INDODAPOER_csv.zip zip;District Proliferation Crosswalk (Excel) (102 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/ind', 'INDO DAPOER, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/indonesia database for policy and economic research', 20, '1976 2013', '', '', '45'),
(102, 113, 'Country Opinion Survey Data', 'COSD', 'Survey data about how the World Bank Group and its work in social and economic development are perceived by key stakeholders in client countries across the globe.', 'http://countrysurveys.worldbank.org/', 'Survey(Microdata)', '', '', 'IBRD, IDA, WLD', 'National, Regional', 0, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Aid Effectiveness, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development, Trade, Urban Development, World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'No fixed schedule', '', '18 Mar 2014', 'countrysurveys@worldbankgroup.org', 'Questionnaires change by country and by year. Each country has two different files (spss, pdf     final report).  We also provide regional reports as they become available.', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'COSD http://microdata.worldbank.org/index.php/catalog/COS/about', 'Country Opinion Survey Data', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/country opinion survey data', 57, '', '', '', ''),
(103, 114, 'Data Resources for Structural Economic Analysis', '', 'Collection of over 60 comprehensive international databases on the structure of the global economy, and standardized metadata for each, covering both technical characteristics of the data and detailed access information. Areas represented in the collection include output and value added by industrial sector, labor force, social and demographic data, productivity, and measures of economic endowments.', 'https://finances.worldbank.org/d/c32c 3558', 'Cross sectional', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'Other', 0, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development', 'No further updates planned', '', '22 Apr 2014', 'data@worldbank.org', 'Overall, about three quarters of the datasets are maintained by international organizations, most with global coverage and a few specific to geographical regions. The vast majority of data resources are available through open access or free user registration; only 16  are fee based or require paid membership or subscription.', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'Data Resources for Structural Economic Analysis (CSV) https://finances.worldbank.org/api/views/c32c 3558/rows.csv;Data Resources for Structural Economic Analysis (API) https://finances.worldbank.org/api/views/c32c 3558/rows.json', 'Data Resources for Structural Economic Analysis, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/structural economic analysis', 101, '', '1', 'https://finances.worldbank.org/d/c32c 3558', ''),
(104, 115, 'All the Ginis Dataset', '', 'This dataset includes combined and standardized Gini data from eight original sources: Luxembourg Income Study (LIS), Socio Economic Database for Latin America (SEDLAC), Survey of Living Conditions (SILC) by Eurostat, World Income Distribution (WYD; the full data set is available here), World Bank Europe and Central Asia dataset, World Institute for Development Research (WIDER), World Bank Povcal, and Ginis from individual long term inequality studies (just introduced in this version).', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 187, 'Economy & Growth, Poverty', 'Annually', 'June', '30 Jun 2013', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'All the Ginis (Excel) http://siteresources.worldbank.org/INTRES/Resources/469232 1107449512766/allginis_2013.xls', 'Branko L. Milanovic, All the Ginis Dataset, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/all the ginis', 58, '1950   2012', '', '', ''),
