(126, 137, 'Professional Services Knowledge Platform Africa', '', 'Professional services, such as accounting & auditing, legal, architectural and engineering services, are critical for Africa   s development.\n<P>\nWhile they are among the most dynamic services sectors in the continent, these sectors remain underdeveloped in many countries. Despite recent progress, obstacles to trade and regulatory heterogeneity still leave the regional markets for professional services fragmented.\n<P>\nIn order to support their integration, this website constitutes a knowledge pl', 'http://worldbank.fissiondev.com/markets/providers', 'Cross sectional', 'English', 'Annual', 'SSA', 'Business or firm', 19, 'Economy & Growth, Private Sector', 'No further updates planned', '', '21 Jan 2015', 'Africa Trade Team: Carmine Soprano, csoprano@worldbank.org <mailto:csoprano@worldbank.org>, Nora Dihel , ndihel@worldbank.org <mailto:ndihel@worldbank.org>', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'Providers dataset (Excel 2.6 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/PSKPAfrica/providers_dataset.xlsx excel;Users indicator dataset (Excel 1.1 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/PSKPAfrica/users_indicator_dataset.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/professional services knowledge platform africa', 8, '', '', '', ''),
(127, 138, 'Export Value Added Database', 'EVAD', '<P>The Export Value Added Database provides information on the domestic value added content of domestic output and exports for 118 countries across 27 sectors of the economy, including 9 commercial services sectors, 3 primary sectors, and 14 manufacturing sectors, spanning intermittent years between 1997 and 2011.</P>\n\n<P>Trade data is usually measured at transaction values, which are gross values, or value added plus domestic and foreign intermediate inputs. The measure of gross exports may und', 'http://wits.worldbank.org/analyticaldata/redirect2evad.aspx', 'Cross sectional;Time series', '', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National, Regional', 118, 'Trade', 'No fixed schedule', '', '10 May 2016', 'Sebastian Saez, ssaez@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'Export Value Added Database (.zip) http://wits.worldbank.org/data/public/trade/EVAD_February2015.zip;Export Value Added Database (.csv) http://wits.worldbank.org/data/public/trade/EVAD_February2015.csv', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/export value added', 12, '1997 2011', '', '', ''),
(128, 139, 'Trade in Services Database', 'TSD', '<P>The Trade in Services Database provides information on annual bilateral services trade flows in Mode 1 (cross border trade) and Mode 2 (consumption abroad) for 199 countries across a multitude of sectors and years spanning 1985 and 2011. The collection of data on cross border trade in services is notoriously difficult, in large part due to the intangible nature of services but also the high capacity needed to record such data. This is particularly true for developing countries. This database ', '', 'Cross sectional;Time series', '', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National, Regional', 195, 'Trade', 'Biannually', 'In the second quarter of every other fiscal year.', '03 Feb 2015', 'Sebastian Saez, ssaez@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'Trade in Services (.zip) http://wits.worldbank.org/data/public/trade/TSD_February2015.zip;Trade in Services(.csv) http://wits.worldbank.org/data/public/trade/TSD_February2015.csv', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/trade in services', 6, '1995 2011', '', '', ''),
(129, 140, 'Gender Highlights: 2012 World Development Report', '', 'The Gender Statistics: Highlights from 2012 World Development Report database provides subset of gender indicators from the 2012 World Development Report on Gender Equality and Development.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source gender statistics : highlights from 2012 world development report', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 214, 'Gender', 'No further updates planned', '', '29 Sep 2011', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', '', 'The data in this dataset are taken from several sources. Please refer to the Technical Notes in the report    WDR 2012: Gender Equality and Development    for more information.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/gender highlights 2012 wdr', 0, '1999   2010', '', '', ''),
(130, 141, 'Country Partnership Strategy for India (FY2013 17)     Project Result Indicators Data', 'IndiaCPS_PDOIndicators', 'An aggregation of result indictors that measure progress against the project development objectives (PDOs) for relevant IBRD and IDA funded projects which are tracked under the World Bank Group Country Partnership Strategy for India for the period 2013 2017. A project development objective conveys what the project intends to achieve and these accompanying results indicators are used to monitor implementation progress.', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Month', 'SAS', 'Project', 1, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Aid Effectiveness, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development, Trade, Urban Development, World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Monthly', 'Updated on the 15th of every month.', '30 Jun 2015', 'data@worldbank.org', 'The dataset includes only the Project Development Objective (PDO) level results indicators that pertain to IBRD and IDA projects tracked under the World Bank Group   s Country Partnership Strategy for India for the period 2013 2017.\n\nThe data in this dataset do not imply any judgment on the part of The World Bank concerning the legal status of the states and union territories of India, nor does it imply endorsement or acceptance of territorial boundaries.', 'Bulk download', 'INDIA CPS_PDOIndicators (228 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/India_CPS_Results.csv csv', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/india cps project result indicators', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(131, 142, 'Comparative Advantage, International Trade, and Fertility', '', 'The paper associated with this dataset analyzes theoretically and empirically the impact of comparative advantage in international trade on fertility. It builds a model in which industries differ in the extent to which they use female relative to male labor and countries are characterized by Ricardian comparative advantage in either female labor or male labor intensive goods.', '', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 149, 'Gender, Health, Trade', 'No further updates planned', '', '01 Jun 2014', 'Quy Toan Do (qdo@worldbank.org)', 'Please refer to the World Bank WP 6930 for further details and documentation.', 'Bulk download', 'Comparative Advantage, International Trade, and Fertility (Excel) (56kb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/DLR_FNLX_data.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/comparative advantage intl trade fertility', 0, '1960   2005', '', '', ''),
(132, 143, 'Readiness for Investment in Sustainable Energy', 'RISE', 'Readiness for Investment in Sustainable Energy (RISE) is a suite of indicators that assesses the legal and regulatory environment for investment in sustainable energy. This dataset contains scores for every single indicator of RISE for each country.', 'http://rise.worldbank.org', 'Cross sectional;Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA', 'National', 17, 'Climate Change, Energy & Mining', 'Biannually', '', '30 Nov 2014', 'rise@worldbankgroup.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', 'Readiness for Investment in Sustainable Energy, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/rise', 0, '2014   2014', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '44'),
(133, 144, 'Subnational Population Database', '', 'Subnational Population Database presents estimated population at the first administrative level below the national level. Many of the data come from the country   s national statistical offices. Other data come from the NASA Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center (SEDAC) managed by the Center for International Earth Science Information Network (CIESIN), Earth Institute, Columbia University. It is the World Bank Group   s first subnational population database at a global level and there are d', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/views/variableselection/selectvariables.aspx source subnational population', 'Geospatial;Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA', 'Sub national', 102, 'Health', 'Annually', '', '21 Sep 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'Subnational Population (Excel) ZIP (520 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Subnational Population_excel.zip excel;Subnational Population (CSV) ZIP (231 KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Subnational Population_csv.zip csv', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/subnational population', 0, '2000   2016', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '50'),
(134, 148, 'Public Financial Management Systems and eServices Global Dataset', 'PFM Systems & eServices Datase', 'This dataset was created as a part of the World Development Report (WDR) 2016 activities, to expand existing FMIS and Open Budget Data dataset by including the current status of Public Financial Management (PFM) systems and related online services, as well as the web links to relevant government web sites in 198 economies. Combined database is called    PFM Systems and e Services    dataset and updated annually (in spreadsheet format; including metadata and statistics). The dataset includes 8 ke', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 198, 'Public Sector', 'Annually', 'August', '24 Aug 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'PFM Systems & eServices Dataset http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS/WB_PFM_eServices_dataset.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/pfm systems eservices dataset', 0, '2014   2017', '', '', ''),
(135, 149, 'Digital Governance Projects Database', 'DG Projects Database', 'As a part of the stock taking exercise initiated by the Integrated Digital Solutions (IDS) Group, a new dataset was created as an inventory of all WBG investments including large ICT/e Gov components for governance/sector reforms since 1995. This global dataset includes the details of ICT investments in six categories, together with the cost, duration, and outcome ratings of completed activities, in addition to key project data extracted from the operations portal. The dataset was released in Ju', '', 'Transactions', 'English', '', 'WLD', 'Project', 0, 'Public Sector, World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Annually', 'August', '24 Aug 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'DG Projects Database http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS/WB_Digital_Gov_Database.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/dg projects database', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(136, 150, 'FMIS and Open Budget Data Global Dataset', 'FMIS & OBD Dataset', 'This database was created as a global dataset presenting the use of Financial Management Information Systems in publishing Open Budget Data in 198 economies (using 20 key and 20 informative indicators). The dataset was released in September 2013, as a part of the FMIS and OBD Study (FMIS and Open Budget Data: Do Governments Report on Where the Money Goes ) and is updated annually to reflect the developments since then. The dataset is being used to monitor the effects of FMIS on publishing budget', '', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 198, 'Public Sector', 'Annually', 'August', '24 Aug 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'FMIS & OBD Dataset http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS/WB_FMIS_OBD_dataset.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/fmis and obd dataset', 0, '2013   2017', '', '', ''),
(137, 151, 'Financial Management Information Systems Database', '', 'Financial Management Information Systems (FMIS) Database contains a rich set of operational data and performance ratings related to all completed and active FMIS projects funded by the World Bank (investment lending with large ICT components) since 1984. In addition to existing project data, details of ICT solutions, cost, duration, and performance of FMIS implementation, and relevant web links are presented for the benefit of task teams, as well as the client countries and development agencies ', '', 'Transactions', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'Project', 78, 'Public Sector, World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Biannually', 'August', '24 Aug 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'FMIS Database http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS/WB_FMIS_Database.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/fmis database', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(138, 152, 'Identification for Development Global Dataset', 'ID4D Dataset', 'The World Bank Group s Identification for Development (ID4D) Initiative aggregated data across 198 economies to estimate the number of individuals without proof of legal identity.\n\nThis document presents:\n\n1) Quantitative data on the number of individuals without access to proof of legal identity split by country, region, and income level;\n\n2) Qualitative data on the Ministries charged with identification & civil registration (CR); the status of enabling legal and regulatory frameworks; and ICT,', '', 'Cross sectional', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 198, 'Public Sector', 'Annually', 'August', '01 Jun 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', '2017 ID4D Global Dataset http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/IDS/WB_ID4D_dataset.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/id4d dataset', 0, '2016', '', '', ''),
(139, 153, 'The Costs of Meeting the 2030 SDG targets on Drinking Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene', '', 'This dataset analyzes the global costs of meeting the 2030 Sustainable Development Goal targets on drinking water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH). The spreadsheet allows recalculation of results at country level by the interested analyst using different data inputs.', '', 'Time series', 'Default English, comma separated list of languages', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 0, 'Infrastructure', 'No further updates planned', '', '12 Feb 2016', 'worldbankwater@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'Master Calculations Global WASH (XLSX 12.7 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/WASH/Master Calculations Global WASH CBA_GLOBAL_PUBLIC_VERSION5.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/global water costing study', 0, '', '', '', '');
