(140, 154, 'Labor Content of Exports Database', 'LACEX', 'The Labor Content of Exports (LACEX) database was developed by Cal   et al. (2016) on the basis of a panel of global input output tables and exports from the Global Trade Analysis Project (GTAP) and employment data from the ILO. The database measure the contribution of labor to a given country   s exports     measured as employees    compensation or wages (LACEX) or the number of jobs (JOCEX). It also uses gross output in place of exports to construct the labor and jobs content of domestic produ', 'http://wits.worldbank.org/analyticaldata/redirect2lacex.aspx', 'Cross sectional;Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 120, 'Labor & Social Protection, Trade', 'No fixed schedule', 'The update of the Export of Value Added Database will be based on the update of the GTAP database, and so does not have a fixed schedule.', '22 Jul 2016', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download, Query tool', 'JOCEX 11sect (812KB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/lacex/JOCEX_11_sectors.xlsx excel;LACEX 24sect (14Mb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/lacex/LACEX_24_sectors.xlsx excel;LACEX 57sect (58Mb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/lacex/LACEX_57_sectors.xlsx excel;JOCEX', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/lacex', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(141, 155, 'Sustainable Development Goals', 'SDGs', 'Relevant indicators drawn from the World Development Indicators, reorganized according to the goals and targets of the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). These indicators may help to monitor SDGs, but they are not always the official indicators for SDG monitoring.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx source sustainable development goals (sdgs)', 'Time series', '(Default English, comma separated list of languages)', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National, Regional', 217, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Aid Effectiveness, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development, Trade, Urban Development', 'Quarterly', 'April, July, September, December', '21 Dec 2017', 'Data@worldbank.org', 'Indicators in this dataset may help to monitor SDGs, but they are not always the official indicators for SDG monitoring.', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'SDG (Excel) ZIP (7 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/SDG_excel.zip excel;SDG (CSV) ZIP (7 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/SDG_csv.zip csv', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/sustainable development goals', 0, '1960   2017', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '46'),
(142, 156, 'Making Power Affordable for Africa and Viable for Its Utilities', '', 'The databases contain all the technical, financial, and tariff data collected through the study  Making power affordable in Africa and viable for its utilities.  The final study and background papers are available at <http://www.worldbank.org/affordableviablepowerforafrica>. The objective of making the database public is to make data collected through the study available to utility companies, regulators, and practitioners to provide benchmarks and help inform analysis. The databases will be upda', '', 'Cross sectional', '', 'Annual', 'SSA', 'National', 48, 'Energy & Mining', 'No further updates planned', '', '26 Oct 2016', 'Chris Trimble (ctrimble@worldbank.org)', '', 'Bulk download', 'Tariff database (7.2Mb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/avpfa/avpfa tariff.xlsx excel;Technical database (700Kb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/avpfa/avpfa technical.xlsx excel;Financial database (1.6Mb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/avpfa/avpfa financial.xlsx ', 'Trimble, Chris; Kojima, Masami; Perez Arroyo, Ines; Mohammadzadeh, Farah. 2016. Financial Viability of Electricity Sectors in Sub Saharan Africa: Quasi Fiscal Deficits and Hidden Costs. Policy Research Working Paper; No. 7788', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/affordable viable power for africa', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(143, 157, 'Content of Deep Trade Agreements', '', 'The dataset on the content of preferential trade agreements (PTAs) maps 52 provisions in 279 PTAs notified at WTO signed between 1958 and 2015. It also includes information about legal enforceability of each provision. The    Trade Agreements    file lists all the agreements available (279) with the coding of 52 provisions. The name and description of all variables is listed in the    read me    sheet. The    read me    sheet also explain the coding of legal enforceability. The    Bilateral Obse', '', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, LAC, MNA, SAS, SSA', 'Other', 189, 'Trade', 'No fixed schedule', '', '05 Feb 2017', 'Alen Mulabdic (amulabdic@worldbank.org); Alberto Osnago (Alberto.Osnago@wto.org); Michele Ruta(mruta@worldbank.org)', '', 'Bulk download', 'Trade Agreements (322Kb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/pta/pta agreements.xls excel;Bilateral Observations (10Mb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/pta/pta bilateral observations.zip excel', 'Hofmann Claudia, Alberto Osnago and Michele Ruta, (2017).  Horizontal Depth: A New Database on the Content of Preferential Trade Agreements . Policy Research working paper; no. WPS 7981. Washington, D.C. : World Bank Group.', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/deep trade agreements', 0, '1958 2015', '', '', ''),
(144, 158, 'Toolkit for Informality Scenario Analysis', '', '   A Toolkit for Informality Scenario Analysis    is a spreadsheet based toolkit that allows researchers and practitioners to project the size of formal and informal labor in almost 100 countries yearly until 2030. The projections are based on the model presented in Loayza (2016),    Informality in the Process of Development and Growth,    Policy Research Working Paper WPS7858, World Bank. The model studies the evolution of the informal sector as it relates to changes in capital, labor force, an', '', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 96, 'Economy & Growth', 'No further updates planned', '', '06 Oct 2016', 'Norman Loayza (nloayza@worldbank.org)', '', 'Bulk download', 'Informality Scenario Analysis Toolkit (10Mb) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/research papers/informality scenario analysis.zip excel', 'Norman Loayza and Claudia Meza Cuadra, A Toolkit for Informality Scenario Analysis, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/informality scenario analysis', 1, '1990 2012', '', '', ''),
(145, 159, 'TCdata360', '', 'TCdata360 provides open data on trade and competitiveness. The site aggregates and visualizes data from multiple sources, inside and outside World Bank Group, and presents it in tandem with other knowledge and resources.', 'http://tcdata360.worldbank.org/topics', 'Time series', 'English', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA', 'National, Regional', 0, 'Economy & Growth, External Debt, Financial Sector, Infrastructure, Private Sector, Science & Technology, Trade', 'Annually', 'Different datasets have different update dates', '09 Jan 2016', 'tcdata360@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', 'TCdata360 (tcdata.worldbank.org), World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/tc data 360', 0, '1953 2016', '1', 'http://tcdata360.worldbank.org/tools', ''),
(146, 160, 'Africa Development for Entrepreneurship', 'D4E', 'The African Data for Entrepreneurs Initiative uses household level datasets available at the World Bank to create summary indicators useful for entrepreneurs in Africa creating or growing their businesses. There are two main sources of data: Listening to Africa and National Household Survey Datasets.\n\nListening to Africa\nL2A is a collaboration with national statistical offices and NGOs in sub Saharan Africa to pilot the use of mobile phones to regularly collect information on living conditions. ', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx source Africa Development Entrepreneurship', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'IDA, LMY, SSA', 'National', 0, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Economy & Growth, Education, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Public Sector, Social Development, Urban Development', 'No fixed schedule', '', '19 Apr 2017', 'Irene Muthoni Ngatia', '', 'Query tool', '', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/africa development entrepreneurship', 0, '2016', '', '', ''),
(147, 161, 'World Bank Procurement Notices', '', '<p>This dataset includes procurement tender notices for World Bank Group financed projects. Learn more about the World Bank Group s operations in procurement at <a href  http://go.worldbank.org/9KQZWXNOI0 >http://go.worldbank.org/9KQZWXNOI0</a></p>.', 'http://www.worldbank.org/projects', 'Transactions', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'Other', 0, 'World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Daily', 'Daily updates when new records are available', 'Current', 'wbfinances@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', 'World Bank Products and Services, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/procurement notices', 0, '', '1', 'http://search.worldbank.org/api/procnotices', ''),
(148, 162, 'World Bank Contract Awards', '', '<p>This set of contract awards includes data on commitments against contracts that were reviewed by the Bank before they were awarded (prior reviewed Bank funded contracts) under IDA/IBRD investment projects and related Trust Funds. This dataset does not list all contracts awarded by the Bank, and should be viewed only as a guide to determine the distribution of major contract commitments among the Bank s member countries.  Supplier Country  represents place of supplier registration, which may o', 'http://www.worldbank.org/projects', 'Transactions', '', '', 'EAP, ECA, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'Project', 0, 'World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'Daily', 'Daily when new records are available', 'Current', 'wbfinances@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', 'World Bank Products and Services, World Bank Group', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/contract awards', 0, '', '1', 'http://search.worldbank.org/api/contractdata', ''),
(149, 163, 'G20 Basic Set of Financial Inclusion Indicators', '', 'The G20 Basic Set of Financial Inclusion data repository includes detailed data from users and providers of financial services. The Basic Set measures both access to financial services (   supply side    data) and usage of services (   demand side    data). The Basic Set covers both individuals and small and medium sized enterprises (SME   s) and includes data from three sources and 192 countries. The five basic set indicators are as follows: 1.The percentage of adults with a formal account; 2. ', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx source g20 financial inclusion indicators', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 216, 'Economy & Growth, Financial Sector', 'No fixed schedule', '', '01 Jun 2016', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/g20 financial inclusion indicators', 0, '2011 2015', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '33'),
(150, 164, 'Commodity Prices: History and Projections', '', 'The World Bank   s Commodity Price historical data and forecasts are published quarterly, in January, April, July and October. The price forecasts go up to 2030.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx source commodity prices  history and projections 2C updated quarterly', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'WLD', 'National', 1, 'Agriculture & Rural Development', 'Quarterly', 'January, April, July and October', '26 Apr 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/commodity prices', 0, '1960 2030', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '55'),
(151, 165, 'WDI Database Archives (beta)', 'WDI DA', 'BETA. The WDI Database Archives (WDI DA) contains previous versions of the World Development Indicators database. Data are drawn from all available electronic releases going back to 1989. Metadata for this initial beta release, however, are only available from the latest WDI database. Users should exercise caution when comparing data from different versions, as the same codes have been used to reference series from different base years or different valuations of a country   s local currency. For', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx source wdi database archives (beta)', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National', 0, 'Agriculture & Rural Development, Aid Effectiveness, Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, External Debt, Financial Sector, Gender, Health, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Poverty, Private Sector, Public Sector, Science & Technology, Social Development, Trade, Urban Development, World Bank Group Projects & Finances', 'No fixed schedule', '', '04 Oct 2016', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Query tool', '', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/wdi database archives', 0, '1950 2015', '1', '', '57'),
(152, 167, 'Thailand Systematic Country Diagnostic', '', 'This excel file contains the data from Thailand Systematic Country Diagnostic Report that we used to create the 60 or so graphs which appear on this report. This is not a preliminary data but it contains the results of some tabulations the report team (using this data set).', '', 'Cross sectional', '', 'Annual', 'EAP', 'National', 1, 'Climate Change, Economy & Growth, Education, Energy & Mining, Environment, Financial Sector, Infrastructure, Labor & Social Protection, Public Sector', 'No further updates planned', '', '29 Jun 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'Bulk download', 'SCD Figures (36 MB) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/Thailand SCD/FiguresusedinThailandSCDUPDATED.xlsx excel', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/thailand scd', 0, '', '', '', ''),
(153, 168, 'Universal Health Coverage Global Monitoring Data', '', 'Universal health coverage (UHC) means that all people can obtain the health services they need without suffering financial hardship. The 2017 UHC Global Monitoring Report looks at how many people globally lack access to essential health services and how many are pushed into poverty or spending too much of their household budgets on out of pocket health expenses.', 'http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx source universal health coverage', 'Time series', '', 'Annual', 'EAP, ECA, HIC, IBRD, IDA, LAC, LMY, MNA, SAS, SSA, WLD', 'National, Regional', 134, 'Economy & Growth, Health', 'Annually', '', '13 Dec 2017', 'data@worldbank.org', '', 'API, Bulk download, Query tool', 'UHC (Excel) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/UHC_EXCEL.zip;UHC (CSV) http://databank.worldbank.org/data/download/UHC_CSV.zip', '', 'http://data.worldbank.org/data catalog/universal health coverage global monitoring data 2017', 0, '1984 2015', '1', 'http://data.worldbank.org/developers', '58'),
